-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Guaranty Trust Bank, UBA Nigeria Move
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-04-20T15:37:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-standard-chartered-kenya-uba-nigeria.html
Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  rose for a
third day, jumping 1.1 percent to 62.14 in Nairobi, the highest
close since Aug. 24.  The  Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index (NGSEINDX)  surged 1.7
percent to 21,756.5 in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement
from the bourse. Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  fell less than 0.1
percent to 1,792.33. The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  gained for a
fourth day, increasing 0.2 percent to 903.63  in Windhoek.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Guaranty Trust Bank Plc (GUARANTY)  , Nigeria’s largest
bank by market value, rose for a fourth day, advancing 2 percent
to 15.72 naira, the highest since June 23, after first-quarter
earnings jumped.  Standard Chartered Bank Kenya Ltd. (SCBL)  , the country’s
fifth-biggest lender, jumped 2.4 percent to 169 shillings after
its directors approved a rights offer plan.  “The capital-raising drive could be a signal of
management’s positive growth outlook,” Nairobi-based Standard
Investment Bank said today in an e-mailed note to clients.  United Bank for Africa Plc  (UBA NL), Nigeria’s sixth
largest lender by market value, surged 4.9 percent to 2.81
naira, a third day of gains and the highest close in more than
six weeks, after reporting first-quarter profit more than
tripled.  To contact the reporter on this story:
